data.text:
Yes, theres life beyond Kent, even for me! This page is for photos and snippets about various places far away from my beloved little corner of the world that Ive visited in recent times and found interesting. Hopefully Ill be able to get some photos and words from friends on here whove had trips to natural environments with a story. So here goes

Southern California

Joshua Tree national park, Temecula, Santa Rosa Plateau, Mt Palomar state park

My first selection is from my trip to see friends in southern California in July 2018 . Huge thanks to them. Photographs  Adam McCulloch

Lavaux district, Vaud canton, Switzerland

I visited this area on the northeastern shores of Lake Geneva in April 2018. I was covering the Cully Jazz festival for Jazzwise and possibly Guardian Travel.

Western Crete

Fantastic gorges, coastline, light, tavernas. An island with more charisma than anywhere else Ive been in the Med. Not the best quality because taken on an iPhone SE.

Brecon Beacons, Powys, Wales

North-west Scotland  Ross and Cromarty and Assynt

A brilliant trip in May 2022 saw a KWNL elite force of three trudgers joined by mountain goat Gav of Glasgow, who led us through bog, up rocky paths, down ludicrously steep slopes and over lively streams to some of the best views Ive ever witnessed. Eagles were spotted in the distance, cuckoos heard incessantly, great skuas and puffins observed on clifftops, while walking boots, calves, knees and hamstrings were given a good workout. We stayed in wonderful Ullapool in a bunk house in an annexe of the Ceilidh Place (very friendly and which serves great food  recommended). What a trip, if only for four days. We climbed the superb Ben Mor Coigach ridge which tumbles spectacularly into the sea opposite the Summer Isles, visited Handa Island up near Durness, walked  well, almost  to the highest waterfall in the UK, and sauntered along Little Loch Bloom. The weather? Pretty good actually, even warm at times but there was some rain too.
